problems.content:
Only printing some items, not all! Lists and <code>if</code> statements are a powerful combo — you can loop through a list and only act on items that match a condition.<br><br>Watch the indenting carefully! The <code>if</code> goes inside the <code>for</code> (2 spaces), and the <code>print</code> goes inside the <code>if</code> (4 spaces — that's double):<pre style='background:#f1f5f9;padding:8px 12px;border-radius:4px;margin:8px 0;'>for num in numbers:
  if num &gt; 5:
    print(num)</pre>

problems.starterCode:
numbers = [2, 8, 3, 10, 1, 7, 4]
for num in numbers:
  print(num)

rules.solutionCode:
numbers = [2, 8, 3, 10, 1, 7, 4]
for num in numbers:
  if num > 5:
    print(num)

numbers = [2, 8, 3, 10, 1, 7, 4]
big = []
for num in numbers:
  if num > 5:
    big.append(num)
print(big)

